.TH "drm_dp_downstream_rgb_to_ycbcr_conversion" 9 "drm_dp_downstream_rgb_to_ycbcr_conversion" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_dp_downstream_rgb_to_ycbcr_conversion \- determine downstream facing port RGB->YCbCr conversion capability
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" drm_dp_downstream_rgb_to_ycbcr_conversion
.BI "(const u8 dpcd[DP_RECEIVER_CAP_SIZE] "  ","
.BI "const u8 port_cap[4] "  ","
.BI "u8 color_spc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dpcd" 12
DisplayPort configuration data
.IP "port_cap" 12
downstream facing port capabilities
.IP "color_spc" 12
Colorspace for which conversion cap is sought
.SH "RETURN"
whether the downstream facing port can convert RGB->YCbCr for a given
colorspace.
